content.detailedDescription: I was standing outside of our townhouse at around midnight last week, windingdown.  i always gaze up at the stars...Its an interest.  in the distance inoticed what would have certainly passed for three stars, only these were movingin an exact triangular formation, at one speed and completely synchronized. coming from the north, i watched as they maintained this exact formation acrossthe sky, and beyond my vision.  the entire sighting lasted about 3 minutes. these objects did not blink, they just moved directly across the night sky at analtitude that appeared almost the same as the stars themselves...It looked asthough they were moving through other stars...I know that is not possible, butthat is the optical illusion that my ground perspective yielded.
content.summary: Triangular formation moving quicky across late eve

content.summary: Saw what looked like a window to another world

content.detailedDescription: On 09-18-02, at approx. 1400 hrs, witnesses were inside of a lake mobile homejust offshore of toledo bend lake, when witness# 1 glanced out of a window tothe residence and noted an approx. 8 foot round circle in the lake.  witness #1called to witness #2 and both went on shore to closer observe the anomaly. there were no other people or boats observed by the witnesses in the area.  eventhough it was raining hard and the wind blew out of the south, the circle didnot dissipate.  also, waves from the wind were noted by the witneses to beoutside the of center and outer edges of the circle, however, the circle itselfremained smooth and undisturbed.  witness #1 took 3 digital photos of thisanamoly, and both witnesses observed the circle slowly elongate and disappearafter about 30 minutes.  note:  witnesses had heard jet aircraft and ahelocopter in the area the day before, which was unusual for the area.
content.summary: Saw unusual water circle in lake

content.detailedDescription: Tonight 9/20/2002, at approximately 7:49 pm central time, i had stepped outsideand i observed what appeared to me to be a orb type ufo that was almost directlyover my house here in elk city, oklahoma. (100 miles west of oklahoma city oni-40).I noticed the object was perfectly round, and it was extremely bright-almost too bright to look at directly at first. i also noted a unusual whiteflorescence to it. on closer examination with my 10 x 50 binoculars, it appearedto have 2-3 internal lights of some kind that were clearly visible, similar to ahot air balloon would have. however, it was not a balloon. no other details werenoted. it flew in a westerly direction roughly following i-40 toward amarillo.After it flew from overhead, and at about a 45 degree angle to the horizon, itstarted to rapidly change colors to a yellow, then a bright red and finally to adeep blu!E-purple internal glow that it maintained until it disappeared.I was able toestimate the object to be at about 5,000 feet, and moving at about 25-30 milesper hour, and it was moving steadily to the west.At the time of the sighting wehad a se wind at 5-7 mph.   the object was in sight until about 8:15 pm when itwinked out as i was watching it through binoculars. it went from about a 80degree overhead angle to about 20 degrees above the horizon in that time. atits closest it was about 1/2 the size of the full moon, or about the size ofyour thumb at arms length.I have eliminated weather balloons, planets, stars,aircraft and blimps as a possible explanation. i did notice venus in thesouthwest sky about 10-15 degrees above the horizon. the object did not resemblevenus or a star. there were no aircraft in the area at the time of thesighting.If anyone else saw this object contact me at:jim@thehickmanreport.Comjim hickmanmufon- research specialist- media operations
content.summary: Orb ufo report
